      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., normalized RMS error) applied to hemolysis index predictions versus experimental measurements with statistical significance assessed.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index predictions compared against experimental data using percent error; mean error 22% across operating points. No statistical significance testing performed. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QOIs (absolute hemolysis index) directly correspond to clinical acceptance threshold; mapping from model output to clinical endpoint documented.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) is directly mapped to the clinical threshold; however, the power-law model computes a surrogate scalar that requires post-processing conversion with documented but unvalidated correction factors. Achieved level 2 against required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
