      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters characterized with probability distributions; Monte Carlo propagation demonstrates input uncertainty contribution to output uncertainty is fully characterized with dominant drivers identified.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed propagating distributions across all model inputs including fluid viscosity, power-law exponents, and boundary conditions. Output uncertainty bands are reported. However, no ranking of input contributions was performed, so the dominant drivers of hemolysis index uncertainty remain unidentified. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
